indimail-mta (2.5-0) unstable; urgency=low

  * qmail-multi.c - fixed qscanq path to sbin
  * fixed do_scan() for badattachment check
  * qmail-remote.c, smtpd.c disable SSLv2, SSLv3 to fix POODLE vulnerability
  * remove hardcoded servicedir in spec file
  * dnsmxip - print host along with ip
  * added foxhole_all.cdb for banned extensions in clamav
  * svctool option --config=foxhole for creating foxhole_all.cdb
  * BUG - do_scan.c - break out of loop if file extension matches a line in badext
  * qmail-remote, qmail-daned - added dane verification code using getdns
  * substdo.c - added subsdio_discard() function to discard unflushed data
  * dns.c - added dns_tlsarr() function to query TLSA records
  * qmail-remote.c - added inbuilt DANE verification function using dns_tlsarr() function
  * qmail-remote.c - added DANE verification function via qmail-daned
  * qmail-remote.c - added tlsadomains control file check
  * qmail-daned.c - removed DANE verification via external DANEPROG script
  * qmail-daned.c - use dns_tlsarr() function.
  * tlsacheck.c - modified for qmail-remote query/update
  * qdane.c - modified for qmail-remote query/update
  * postinstall - create DANE verification service only if TLSA code is compiled
  * removed calls to gethostbyname - tcpopen.c, udpopen.c, qmail-daned.c, qmail-greyd.c, udplogger.c, tablematch.c
  * added qmail-daned service to refresh list
  * dnstlsarr program - cmd line DANE validation tool

 -- Manvendra Bhangui <manvendra@indimail.org>  Thu, 31 May 2018 17:25:37 +0530
